17-Year-Old boy Sues His Parents for Being Broke while they are White A 17-year-old is undertaking one of the most controversial lawsuits of the history of the country as he is suing his own biological parents for being too broke whike they are born white.Anthony Dwight, 17, claims he has suffered his whole life from the shame of being broke and white at the same time. &#8220;When I was a kid, I&#8217;d spend hours in the shower trying to wash off the white of my skin, but it would never go away,&#8221; he recalls painfully. &#8220;Isn&#8217;t there enough white people on this planet already? Haven&#8217;t we inflicted enough suffering, racism and oppression in this world?&#8221; he asked reporters. Anthony Dwight, who plans to change his name to Jamal Freeman, is asking that his parents pay for the $20,000 skin coloring treatment he needs to turn his skin color to &#8220;dark black&#8221; he told reporters.